<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503525>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 6-13. Right branches of forceps in South-East Asian species of Nala Zacher, 1910. 6 – N. tenuicornis (Bormans, 1900); 7 – N. timorensis Brindle, 1967; 8 – N. nepalensis (Burr, 1907); 9 – N. ornata Borelli, 1932; 10 – N. basalis Bey-Bienko, 1970; 11- N. lividipes (Dufour, 1829); 12 – N. alenae sp. nov. Scale bar = 1 mm. Adopted from BRINDLE (1966), BEY-BIENKO (1970), STEINMANN (1989b) and SRIVASTAVA (2003)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4503525/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4503521>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 1-5. Nala alenae sp. nov. 1 – habitus of male, dorsal view; 2 – right branch of male forceps, dorsal view; 3 – right branch of female forceps, dorsal view; 4 – subgenital plate of male, dorsal view; 5 – male genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4503521/files/figure.png" .

